Liability charges can be levied against a divorced dad who fails to pay a support to his children or who brings up his child in grievous conditions.

A divorced father has to fulfill at least a number of social duties like paying monthly drawings until he dies.

Why does Hungarian attorney disagree with the current regulations?

In an attempt to achieve higher divorce rates and the consequent birth of new families, the Hungarian Ministry of Justice calls for the removal of legal obstacles to divorce.

The current number of men who prove that they do fulfill their social duties shows that divorce regulations in Hungary may need some kind of amendment.

One can say that the influence of burdened fathers is stronger than any potential benefits for both children and divorced fathers. Hungarian attorney is not surprised to see a lagging number of Hungarian fathers who propose any changes to the divorce condition in their favor. Probably, anyone who has a relationship with divorced people is in touch with emotionally-triggering stories which prevent society from changing the state of things.

See the rest of the article and statistical assumptions here: http://hungarytoday.hu/news/marriage-divorce-dangerous-pursuit-hungarian-fathers-face-high-chance-violation-procedural-rules-28840
